DIV1.P:
The Almighty Governor of the universe, claims it as a prerogative annexed to his royalty, to govern all the events that take place;
"To do his pleasure in the armies of Heaven above, and amongst the inhabitants of this lower world"
—He sendeth war, and he createth peace. He saves and he destroys. This government and superintendance of the world, is but the exercise, of those perfections, which are inherent in him▪ and the necessary and certain consequence of those essential attributes, which properly belong to Deity. Else why do we so often see the finger of an Invisible Being, deep∣ly imprinted on the affairs of the world; unless we sup∣pose those perfections, and those attributes, are exert∣ed to govern this immense system and to preserve the order and harmony thereof?
